modules.description: This module provides radix trie-based HTTP route matching with typed parameter extraction, supporting operations to define and compose paths, query parameters, and HTTP method handlers. It works with structured types like `path`, `query`, and `request_target`, enabling precise route definitions through combinators and typed captures (e.g., integers, booleans, custom types) while ensuring type-safe handler execution. It is particularly useful for building type-safe web routers that handle complex URL patterns, query strings, and method-specific logic in OCaml applications.
